</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="34AD6563067AF15D3312EACEB027ED0D" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="7C0836E8067AF15D3312EACEB027ED0D" blockId="1.[113,752,253,373]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D3312EACEB2B3ED6D" bold="true" box="[113,248,253,277]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is a combination of two words: “Vietna”, from part of the name of the country of origin of its 
<typeStatus id="A30C884A067AF15D339CEB0DB366ED2E" box="[255,301,318,342]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">type</typeStatus>
species, while the end part refers to the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="BBB74D6B067AF15D326EEB6DB32AED0D" box="[269,353,350,373]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Erigone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D326EEB6DB32AED0D" box="[269,353,350,373]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Erigone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="34AD6563067AF15D3312EBAEB0F7EFCD" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7C0836E8067AF15D3312EBAEB024ED8D" blockId="1.[112,752,413,501]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D3312EBAEB2ADEDCD" bold="true" box="[113,230,413,437]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The genus contains erigonines with a total length of 1.50–1.78, which are characterised by the following combination of somatic and genital characters:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7C0836E8067AF15D3312E82EB309EE2D" blockId="1.[113,751,541,949]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
1) carapace unmodified in both sexes, cephalic pits absent (see 
<figureCitation id="E48C2A6D067AF15D33A8E80EB37EEE2D" box="[203,309,573,597]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[135,179,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[138,1473,351,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-8@2.[120,1488,349,1897]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Habitus of Vietnagone silvatica, new species (1–3) and Nasoonaria pseudoembolica, new species (4–6). 1, 4, male holotype; 2, 3, 5, 6, female paratype; 1, 2, 4, 5, dorsal view; 3, 6, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577001" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577001/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Figs. 1, 2</figureCitation>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7C0836E8067AF15D3312E86EB07BEE0D" blockId="1.[113,751,541,949]" box="[113,560,605,630]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">2) chelicerae strong, a mastidion absent;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7C0836E8067AF15D3312E84EB3BBEECD" blockId="1.[113,751,541,949]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">3) chaetotaxy formula: 2.2.1.1; all metatarsi with a trichobothrium; TmI 0.39–0.44;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7C0836E8067AF15D3312E88EB090EEAD" blockId="1.[113,751,541,949]" box="[113,731,701,725]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
4) palpal tibia relatively large, modified (see 
<figureCitation id="E48C2A6D067AF15D3105E88EB084EEAD" box="[614,719,701,725]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,157,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[115,1451,323,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-13@3.[109,1461,312,1895]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–13. Details of palpal and epigynal structure of Vietnagone silvatica, new species. 7–10, male holotype; 12, 13, female paratype. 7, left palp, retrolateral view; 8, 9, palpal tibia, prolateral and dorsal views, respectively; 10, distal suprategular apophysis, lateral view; 11, embolic division; 12, 13, epigyne, ventral and dorsal views, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577003" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577003/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Figs. 7–9</figureCitation>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7C0836E8067AF15D3312E8EEB0E2EE8D" blockId="1.[113,751,541,949]" box="[113,681,733,757]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
5) median membrane strongly reduced (see 
<figureCitation id="E48C2A6D067AF15D313BE8EEB0D1EE8D" box="[600,666,733,757]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,157,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[115,1451,323,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-13@3.[109,1461,312,1895]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–13. Details of palpal and epigynal structure of Vietnagone silvatica, new species. 7–10, male holotype; 12, 13, female paratype. 7, left palp, retrolateral view; 8, 9, palpal tibia, prolateral and dorsal views, respectively; 10, distal suprategular apophysis, lateral view; 11, embolic division; 12, 13, epigyne, ventral and dorsal views, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577003" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577003/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7C0836E8067AF15D3312E8CEB2BEEF4D" blockId="1.[113,751,541,949]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
6) distal suprategular apophysis moderately developed (see 
<figureCitation id="E48C2A6D067AF15D33F4E92EB2ACEF4D" box="[151,231,797,821]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,157,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[115,1451,323,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-13@3.[109,1461,312,1895]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–13. Details of palpal and epigynal structure of Vietnagone silvatica, new species. 7–10, male holotype; 12, 13, female paratype. 7, left palp, retrolateral view; 8, 9, palpal tibia, prolateral and dorsal views, respectively; 10, distal suprategular apophysis, lateral view; 11, embolic division; 12, 13, epigyne, ventral and dorsal views, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577003" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577003/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7C0836E8067AF15D3312E90EB3ADEF2D" blockId="1.[113,751,541,949]" box="[113,486,829,853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">7) radix small, convector present;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7C0836E8067AF15D3312E96EB03FEF0D" blockId="1.[113,751,541,949]" box="[113,628,861,885]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
8) embolus whip-shaped, looped (see 
<figureCitation id="E48C2A6D067AF15D3174E96EB02CEF0D" box="[535,615,861,885]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,157,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[115,1451,323,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-13@3.[109,1461,312,1895]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–13. Details of palpal and epigynal structure of Vietnagone silvatica, new species. 7–10, male holotype; 12, 13, female paratype. 7, left palp, retrolateral view; 8, 9, palpal tibia, prolateral and dorsal views, respectively; 10, distal suprategular apophysis, lateral view; 11, embolic division; 12, 13, epigyne, ventral and dorsal views, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577003" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577003/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7C0836E8067AF15D3312E94EB0A9EFED" blockId="1.[113,751,541,949]" box="[113,738,893,917]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
9) abdomen with a pattern in both sexes (see 
<figureCitation id="E48C2A6D067AF15D310FE94EB09FEFED" box="[620,724,893,917]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[135,179,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[138,1473,351,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-8@2.[120,1488,349,1897]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Habitus of Vietnagone silvatica, new species (1–3) and Nasoonaria pseudoembolica, new species (4–6). 1, 4, male holotype; 2, 3, 5, 6, female paratype; 1, 2, 4, 5, dorsal view; 3, 6, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577001" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577001/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Figs. 1–3</figureCitation>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7C0836E8067AF15D3312E9AEB0F7EFCD" blockId="1.[113,751,541,949]" box="[113,700,925,949]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
10)epigyne without a distinct cavity (see 
<figureCitation id="E48C2A6D067AF15D315BE9AEB0CFEFCD" box="[568,644,925,949]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[135,179,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[138,1473,351,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-8@2.[120,1488,349,1897]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Habitus of Vietnagone silvatica, new species (1–3) and Nasoonaria pseudoembolica, new species (4–6). 1, 4, male holotype; 2, 3, 5, 6, female paratype; 1, 2, 4, 5, dorsal view; 3, 6, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577001" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577001/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="E48C2A6D067AF15D31F1E9AEB0FBEFCD" box="[658,688,925,949]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,157,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[115,1451,323,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-13@3.[109,1461,312,1895]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–13. Details of palpal and epigynal structure of Vietnagone silvatica, new species. 7–10, male holotype; 12, 13, female paratype. 7, left palp, retrolateral view; 8, 9, palpal tibia, prolateral and dorsal views, respectively; 10, distal suprategular apophysis, lateral view; 11, embolic division; 12, 13, epigyne, ventral and dorsal views, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577003" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577003/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="34AD6563067AF15D3312E9EEB3D0E98D" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7C0836E8067AF15D3312E9EEB323E92D" blockId="1.[112,752,989,1365]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D3312E9EEB315EF8D" bold="true" box="[113,350,989,1013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
Based on the male palp conformation and somatic characters (see items 2–4, 7 from the list above), the new genus is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="BBB74D6B067AF15D32CFEE2EB0F5E84D" authority="Oi, 1960" authorityName="Oi" authorityYear="1960" box="[428,702,1053,1077]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Gongylidioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D32CFEE2EB01BE84D" box="[428,592,1053,1077]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Gongylidioides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="18264B19067AF15D3138EE2EB0F5E84D" author="Oi R" box="[603,702,1053,1077]" firstAuthor="Oi" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Institute of Polytechnics Osaka City University" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" pagination="137 - 244" part="11" refId="ref3033" refString="Oi R (1960) Linyphiid spiders of Japan. Journal of the Institute of Polytechnics Osaka City University 11 (D): 137 - 244." title="Linyphiid spiders of Japan" type="journal article" year="1960">Oi, 1960</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but distinguished by the unusual shape of the palpal tibia (
<figureCitation id="E48C2A6D067AF15D31D9EE0EB2D1E80D" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,157,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[115,1451,323,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-13@3.[109,1461,312,1895]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–13. Details of palpal and epigynal structure of Vietnagone silvatica, new species. 7–10, male holotype; 12, 13, female paratype. 7, left palp, retrolateral view; 8, 9, palpal tibia, prolateral and dorsal views, respectively; 10, distal suprategular apophysis, lateral view; 11, embolic division; 12, 13, epigyne, ventral and dorsal views, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577003" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577003/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Figs. 7–9</figureCitation>
cf. 
<figureCitation id="E48C2A6D067AF15D33AAEE6EB3A0E80D" box="[201,491,1117,1141]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[135,179,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[138,1473,351,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-8@2.[120,1488,349,1897]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Habitus of Vietnagone silvatica, new species (1–3) and Nasoonaria pseudoembolica, new species (4–6). 1, 4, male holotype; 2, 3, 5, 6, female paratype; 1, 2, 4, 5, dorsal view; 3, 6, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577001" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577001/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Figs. 1G, 2H, 3H, 5G, 6G</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="18264B19067AF15D3170EE6DB0F1E80D" author="Tu LH &amp; Li SQ" box="[531,698,1117,1141]" firstAuthor="Tu" journalOrPublisher="Revue suisse de Zoologie" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" pagination="51 - 65" part="113" refId="ref3174" refString="Tu LH &amp; Li SQ (2006) A review of Gongylidioides spiders (Araneae: Linyphiidae: Erigoninae) from China. Revue suisse de Zoologie, 113: 51 - 65." title="A review of Gongylidioides spiders (Araneae: Linyphiidae: Erigoninae) from China" type="journal article" year="2006">Tu &amp; Li, 2006</bibRefCitation>
), the peculiar structure of the convector, which in 
<taxonomicName id="BBB74D6B067AF15D310DEE4DB0A2E8ED" authority="Tanasevitch, 2019" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2019" box="[622,745,1150,1173]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Vietnagone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D310DEE4DB0A2E8ED" box="[622,745,1150,1173]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Vietnagone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="55F05781067AF15D3312EEADB2A6E8CE" box="[113,237,1182,1206]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" rank="genus">new genus</taxonomicNameLabel>
is divided into two parts (vs. unipartite in 
<taxonomicName id="BBB74D6B067AF15D3312EE8EB35FE8AD" authorityName="Oi" authorityYear="1960" box="[113,276,1213,1237]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Gongylidioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D3312EE8EB35FE8AD" box="[113,276,1213,1237]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Gongylidioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see 
<bibRefCitation id="18264B19067AF15D3233EE8DB3BDE8AD" author="Tu LH &amp; Li SQ" box="[336,502,1213,1237]" firstAuthor="Tu" journalOrPublisher="Revue suisse de Zoologie" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" pagination="51 - 65" part="113" refId="ref3174" refString="Tu LH &amp; Li SQ (2006) A review of Gongylidioides spiders (Araneae: Linyphiidae: Erigoninae) from China. Revue suisse de Zoologie, 113: 51 - 65." title="A review of Gongylidioides spiders (Araneae: Linyphiidae: Erigoninae) from China" type="journal article" year="2006">Tu &amp; Li, 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="18264B19067AF15D3167EE8EB08FE8AD" author="Song YJ &amp; Li SQ" box="[516,708,1213,1237]" firstAuthor="Song" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" pagination="703 - 715" part="35" refId="ref3061" refString="Song YJ &amp; Li SQ (2010) Three new record genera and three new species of Erigoninae from China (Araneae, Linyphiidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 35: 703 - 715." title="Three new record genera and three new species of Erigoninae from China (Araneae, Linyphiidae)" type="journal article" year="2010">Song &amp; Li, 2010</bibRefCitation>
), as well as by the structure of the epigyne, namely the fused lateral walls covering the epigynal cavity (vs. spaced lateral walls in 
<taxonomicName id="BBB74D6B067AF15D33B7EF2EB332E94D" authorityName="Oi" authorityYear="1960" box="[212,377,1309,1333]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Gongylidioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D33B7EF2EB332E94D" box="[212,377,1309,1333]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Gongylidioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<figureCitation id="E48C2A6D067AF15D32EAEF2EB392E94D" box="[393,473,1309,1333]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,157,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[115,1451,323,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-13@3.[109,1461,312,1895]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–13. Details of palpal and epigynal structure of Vietnagone silvatica, new species. 7–10, male holotype; 12, 13, female paratype. 7, left palp, retrolateral view; 8, 9, palpal tibia, prolateral and dorsal views, respectively; 10, distal suprategular apophysis, lateral view; 11, embolic division; 12, 13, epigyne, ventral and dorsal views, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577003" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577003/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
cf. 
<figureCitation id="E48C2A6D067AF15D316AEF2EB2D9E92D" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[135,179,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[138,1473,351,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-8@2.[120,1488,349,1897]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Habitus of Vietnagone silvatica, new species (1–3) and Nasoonaria pseudoembolica, new species (4–6). 1, 4, male holotype; 2, 3, 5, 6, female paratype; 1, 2, 4, 5, dorsal view; 3, 6, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577001" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577001/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Figs. 1H, 2I, 3I, 4C, 6H</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="18264B19067AF15D33DBEF0DB316E92D" author="Tu LH &amp; Li SQ" box="[184,349,1341,1365]" firstAuthor="Tu" journalOrPublisher="Revue suisse de Zoologie" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" pagination="51 - 65" part="113" refId="ref3174" refString="Tu LH &amp; Li SQ (2006) A review of Gongylidioides spiders (Araneae: Linyphiidae: Erigoninae) from China. Revue suisse de Zoologie, 113: 51 - 65." title="A review of Gongylidioides spiders (Araneae: Linyphiidae: Erigoninae) from China" type="journal article" year="2006">Tu &amp; Li, 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7C0836E8067AF15D3312EF4EB3D0E98D" blockId="1.[113,751,1405,1526]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D3312EF4EB304E9ED" bold="true" box="[113,335,1405,1429]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Species included.</emphasis>
The genus contains two species: 
<taxonomicName id="BBB74D6B067AF15D3312EFADB31EE9CD" authority="Tanasevitch, 2019" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2019" box="[113,341,1437,1461]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Vietnagone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvatica" status="new species">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D3312EFADB31EE9CD" box="[113,341,1437,1461]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Vietnagone silvatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="55F05781067AF15D3205EFADB3A6E9CD" box="[358,493,1437,1461]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
(the 
<typeStatus id="A30C884A067AF15D314FEFADB010E9CE" box="[556,603,1438,1462]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">type</typeStatus>
species) and 
<taxonomicName id="BBB74D6B067AF15D3312EF8DB3A3E9AD" authority="(Song &amp; Li, 2010)" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Song &amp; Li" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[113,488,1469,1493]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Vietnagone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugulosa" status="new combination">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D3312EF8DB2B0E9AD" box="[113,251,1469,1493]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">V. rugulosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="18264B19067AF15D326CEF8EB3ABE9AD" author="Song YJ &amp; Li SQ" box="[271,480,1469,1493]" firstAuthor="Song" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" pagination="703 - 715" part="35" refId="ref3061" refString="Song YJ &amp; Li SQ (2010) Three new record genera and three new species of Erigoninae from China (Araneae, Linyphiidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 35: 703 - 715." title="Three new record genera and three new species of Erigoninae from China (Araneae, Linyphiidae)" type="journal article" year="2010">Song &amp; Li, 2010</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="55F05781067AF15D329AEF8DB08EE9AD" box="[505,709,1469,1493]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" rank="species">new combination</taxonomicNameLabel>
, ex 
<taxonomicName id="BBB74D6B067AF15D3312EFEEB3D3E98D" authority="Menge, 1868" authorityName="Menge" authorityYear="1868" box="[113,408,1501,1526]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Gongylidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D3312EFEEB2B7E98D" box="[113,252,1501,1525]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Gongylidium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="18264B19067AF15D3266EFEDB3D3E98D" author="Menge A" box="[261,408,1501,1526]" firstAuthor="Menge" journalOrPublisher="Schriften der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft in Danzig (N. F.)" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" pagination="153 - 218" part="2" refId="ref2974" refString="Menge A (1868) Preussische Spinnen. II. Abtheilung. Schriften der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft in Danzig (N. F.) 2: 153 - 218." title="Preussische Spinnen. II. Abtheilung" type="journal article" year="1868">Menge, 1868</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
